# Enclosures

Enclosures are the physical habitats placed on the tile grid that house animals. Each enclosure belongs to a biome type, has a condition that degrades over time, and can be repaired or upgraded through three tiers. The player must balance expansion (more enclosures) with maintenance (keeping existing ones in good condition).

## Biome Definitions

```js
export const BIOME = {
  savanna: {
    name: 'Savanna',
    baseCost: 500,
    baseCapacity: 3,
    maintenanceCostPerTick: 0.2,
    defaultWidth: 4,
    defaultHeight: 4,
    fillColor: '#c8b060',
    borderColor: '#a08830',
    description: 'Open grassland for plains animals. Houses lions, elephants, giraffes.',
